[
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.1",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Lo, mine eye hath seen all {this}, mine ear hath heard and understood it.",
    "hash": "11de204da6b0cfcd8f82cf3cd47789ba6b3f97de8f1c43fb6c0f5ac8e9478aa9"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.2",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "What ye know, {the same} do I know also: I {am} not inferior unto you.",
    "hash": "657c3948cd7c2a030b82a1f1642c807dfce16215c66575cfbaf6fc0b17586b10"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.3",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Surely I would speak to the Almighty, and I desire to reason with God.",
    "hash": "972c752c241d045a9ddc806898bb69b454948843f1591adcebdec66c75b0a2ba"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.4",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "But ye {are} forgers of lies, ye {are} all physicians of no value.",
    "hash": "6ea02dde6c137dbc0cea10b8c7067015211005eeb3eb6199d4bccd488b8b2ecd"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.5",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "O that ye would altogether hold your peace! and it should be your wisdom.",
    "hash": "5b8c7a124c333c3b2d874f8248c1d999dcd59a89a08ab5e5715d3a30a0c671a7"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.6",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Hear now my reasoning, and hearken to the pleadings of my lips.",
    "hash": "641cdd9fcb428ded1c767b2c441b980224b0dac228d344ea8c304eb36e9ab076"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.7",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Will ye speak wickedly for God? and talk deceitfully for him?",
    "hash": "41f7d0b69acdac3b0bd51f9052109adfabf3cd2494cdaeee1ba77048fb0481bf"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.8",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Will ye accept his person? will ye contend for God?",
    "hash": "3cf1220ebb1065ccdc06225fd96f5da7cb05d21f01fe6ffd0a26c4b9a3e81ce1"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.9",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Is it good that he should search you out? or as one man mocketh another, do ye {so} mock him?",
    "hash": "fa027fd48a1a081047a44ddff270cbfdcd3d1ec595e4db9533a8b6fed98589ba"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.10",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "He will surely reprove you, if ye do secretly accept persons.",
    "hash": "b5e920060ee609623a1a7613cf984dd5d1ec7cbefb91e316f55a40349d4226af"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.11",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Shall not his excellency make you afraid? and his dread fall upon you?",
    "hash": "a37b5199db616c0c9bac99e54c53e842f3352f6a9028b6a54c1fdaa301066eeb"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.12",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Your remembrances {are} like unto ashes, your bodies to bodies of clay.",
    "hash": "8c4edd9b8b034726edb74694cacb2968969a2a2b9e20dbca37da4c35e1aab4d5"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.13",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Hold your peace, let me alone, that I may speak, and let come on me what {will}. {Hold...: Heb. Be silent from me}",
    "hash": "993dbce4c86bddeb5755bad68ab929442ba59055cb8bfda5929c6386ec45c88f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.14",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Wherefore do I take my flesh in my teeth, and put my life in mine hand?",
    "hash": "7fd6890019c5f069a726c74b6eee756a49bd0e5e77681875c44115c32dcc3714"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.15",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Though he slay me, yet will I trust in him: but I will maintain mine own ways before him. {maintain: Heb. prove, or, argue}",
    "hash": "5bbe46b832b895ada1983f540ae78dd87af8b12b5f26c57215f0f162e9d9ab22"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.16",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "He also {shall be} my salvation: for an hypocrite shall not come before him.",
    "hash": "be2c43df619b7dcbacd6aaf6b7871dac9c778c3ba1fdc4ac168834f9dae9bb6b"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.17",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Hear diligently my speech, and my declaration with your ears.",
    "hash": "998d970a2bfc34b56f6eb1f7363d34662930f456a7dd0c7bca04df7e6316dcfb"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.18",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Behold now, I have ordered {my} cause; I know that I shall be justified.",
    "hash": "44b2595287007cf17b92af5bde026bb3c39e76aa5ea0a90e6b99d614990fc456"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.19",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Who {is} he {that} will plead with me? for now, if I hold my tongue, I shall give up the ghost.",
    "hash": "d335bf70723bb14bafb30ef459f499ce4ef54f7c4cc48b8e8c4854a183c54abc"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.20",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Only do not two {things} unto me: then will I not hide myself from thee.",
    "hash": "e82dc842f885b9573a4e3f02229eb0ef77e34891e7710ce54de3f04769203002"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.21",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Withdraw thine hand far from me: and let not thy dread make me afraid.",
    "hash": "9f3a85f29ee1a20f82e5de07361be510978d5ff0a799827efac51ef225d40226"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.22",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "Then call thou, and I will answer: or let me speak, and answer thou me.",
    "hash": "667e0d6403d89802883154eb9f8fa1ca75a180f608ec946bc86963565af1188b"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.23",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "How many {are} mine iniquities and sins? make me to know my transgression and my sin.",
    "hash": "4cab73956237023482c6bfe36501ced4fc9503ec16112e49b35dc40857c9bcf8"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.24",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Wherefore hidest thou thy face, and holdest me for thine enemy?",
    "hash": "7fbe88c22547a797c2edc6990fa8a22122a168c6c27ec9f9e75b3b3d31a584df"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.25",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Wilt thou break a leaf driven to and fro? and wilt thou pursue the dry stubble?",
    "hash": "b6ee243b4d8c472e0c0b731cfc0e6e6aeae81094a1dfe1cf6d6023a9fa8024ff"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.26",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "For thou writest bitter things against me, and makest me to possess the iniquities of my youth.",
    "hash": "6ee6422dd0abb9a94fa48cb32731befdec5d1aef52ec09de39e4ea0e9cd22a50"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.27",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Thou puttest my feet also in the stocks, and lookest narrowly unto all my paths; thou settest a print upon the heels of my feet. {lookest...: Heb. observest} {heels: Heb. roots}",
    "hash": "ddfbf02b7d235386614e85d5a4c15c7ba346e8ca9cc90efa9a171b048e77d2b2"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.13.28",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And he, as a rotten thing, consumeth, as a garment that is moth eaten.",
    "hash": "c7d87b164f2e99951b286819323527d7f729011acd936459363b0b19cfde2dd3"
  }
]